  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2017-02-07T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Universal Savings Account Act\n\nThis bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow for the establishment of Universal Savings Accounts. These accounts shall be tax-exempt and may be opened by any individual who is at least 18 years of age and a U.S. citizen or legal permanent resident. Contributions to these accounts must be in cash and may not exceed $5,500 (adjusted annually for inflation) in any calendar year. Distributions from a Universal Savings Account are excluded from the gross income of the account holder for income tax purposes."
  }, 
